caption:
Table 6: In this ablation study we show the classification accuracy in the testing set of CIFAR-10 

and CIFAR-100 under symmetric and asymmetric noises at several rates. First, we show the 

results of self-supervised pre-training using the current SOTA SCAN [10] (first two rows, with the 

results with (*) produced by locally running the published code provided by the authors). Then 

we show the current SOTA SSL learning for noisy label DivideMix [7]. Next, we show the results 

of DivideMix pre-trained with SCAN. The last row shows our ScanMix that combines SSL and 

semantic clustering. The top results within 1% are highlighted in bold.
